{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddb6c897a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1150c"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1150c"},"text":"§ 1150c.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Self-hauling of hay or other roughages under hay transportation assistance program; liability for or refund of excess payments; availability of funds for payments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Notwithstanding any other provision of law, no persons who have received or have owing to them, prior to ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-24"},"text":"September 24, 1980","children":[],"tail":", payments at rates announced by the Secretary of Agriculture for self-hauling of hay or other roughages under the hay transportation assistance program shall be liable for, or be obligated to refund, any amount that is determined by the Secretary to be in excess of the payment computed in accordance with the maximum rate provided by section 8 of the Farmer-to-Consumer Direct Marketing Act of 1976: "},{"tag":"i","attrib":{},"text":"Provided","children":[],"tail":", That the Secretary determines that such persons have otherwise complied with the terms and conditions of, and are otherwise entitled to payments under, the hay transportation assistance program. Any payments made pursuant to this section shall be made out of funds appropriated or otherwise available on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-24"},"text":"September 24, 1980","children":[],"tail":" for disaster relief."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddb6c897b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-12-20/ch623/s4"},"text":"Dec. 20, 1944, ch. 623, § 4","children":[],"tail":", as added "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/356"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–356","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1177"},"text":"94 Stat. 1177","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddb6c897c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddb6c897d-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddb6c897e-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 8 of the Farmer-to-Consumer Direct Marketing Act of 1976, referred to in text, is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/463/s8"},"text":"section 8 of Pub. L. 94–463","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-08"},"text":"Oct. 8, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/1983"},"text":"90 Stat. 1983","children":[],"tail":", which is set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5145"},"text":"section 5145 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddb6c897f-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“This section” and “","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-24"},"text":"September 24, 1980","children":[],"tail":"”, referred to in the last sentence, were in the original “this Act” and “the date of enactment of this Act”. These references were editorially translated as "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/356"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–356","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1980-09-24"},"text":"Sept. 24, 1980","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/94/1177"},"text":"94 Stat. 1177","children":[],"tail":" and the date of enactment of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/96/356"},"text":"Pub. L. 96–356","children":[],"tail":", as the probable intent of Congress."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"iddb6c8980-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 1150c, ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1944-12-20/ch623/s4"},"text":"act Dec. 20, 1944, ch. 623, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/58/837"},"text":"58 Stat. 837","children":[],"tail":", related to false representations, acceptance of fees, etc., prior to repeal by act "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-06-25"},"text":"June 25, 1948","children":[],"tail":", 645 § 21, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/862"},"text":"62 Stat. 862","children":[],"tail":", effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":". See sections 217 and 1026 of Title 18, Crimes and Criminal Procedure."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
